{"word":"ἐντήκω","slug":"ἐντήκω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐντήκω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ξω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to pour in while molten</i>, <el>μόλιβδον</el> <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, with <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <el>ἐντέτηκα</el>, <p/></div><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>of feelings, <i>to sink deep in</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of persons, <i>to be absorbed by</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}